events.description: Sikandar Lodi succeeds Bahlul Khan Lodi as Sultan of Delhi.
events.html: • 1489 – Sikandar Lodi succeeds Bahlul Khan Lodi as Sultan of Delhi.[2]

events.html: • 1717 – King George I of Great Britain sails down the River Thames with a barge of 50 musicians, where George Frideric Handel's Water Music is premiered.

events.description: Former emperor Peter III of Russia is murdered.
events.html: • 1762 – Former emperor Peter III of Russia is murdered.

events.description: Bloody Falls massacre: Chipewyan chief Matonabbee, traveling as the guide to Samuel Hearne on his Arctic overland journey, massacres a group of unsuspecting Inuit.

events.description: The 16 Carmelite Martyrs of Compiègne are executed ten days prior to the end of the French Revolution's Reign of Terror.
events.html: • 1794 – The 16 Carmelite Martyrs of Compiègne are executed ten days prior to the end of the French Revolution's Reign of Terror.

events.description: The Kingdom of Spain cedes the territory of Florida to the United States.
events.html: • 1821 – The Kingdom of Spain cedes the territory of Florida to the United States.[3]

events.description: Vega became the first star (other than the Sun) to be photographed.
events.html: • 1850 – Vega became the first star (other than the Sun) to be photographed.[4][5]

events.description: NEC Corporation is organized as the first Japanese joint venture with foreign capital.
events.html: • 1899 – NEC Corporation is organized as the first Japanese joint venture with foreign capital.

events.description: Liner Deutschland sets east to west transatlantic record of five days, eleven hours and five minutes.
events.html: • 1901 – Liner Deutschland sets east to west transatlantic record of five days, eleven hours and five minutes.[6]

events.description: Willis Carrier creates the first air conditioner in Buffalo, New York.
events.html: • 1902 – Willis Carrier creates the first air conditioner in Buffalo, New York.

events.description: King George V issues a proclamation stating that the male line descendants of the British royal family will bear the surname Windsor.
events.html: • 1917 – King George V issues a proclamation stating that the male line descendants of the British royal family will bear the surname Windsor.

events.description: Tsar Nicholas II of Russia and his immediate family and retainers are executed by Bolshevik Chekists at the Ipatiev House in Yekaterinburg, Russia.
events.html: • 1918 – Tsar Nicholas II of Russia and his immediate family and retainers are executed by Bolshevik Chekists at the Ipatiev House in Yekaterinburg, Russia.[7]

events.description: The RMS Carpathia, the ship that rescued the 705 survivors from the RMS Titanic, is sunk off Ireland by the German SM U-55; five lives are lost.
events.html: • 1918 – The RMS Carpathia, the ship that rescued the 705 survivors from the RMS Titanic, is sunk off Ireland by the German SM U-55; five lives are lost.

events.description: The form of government in the Republic of Finland is officially confirmed. For this reason, July 17 is known as the Day of Democracy (Kansanvallan päivä) in Finland.
events.html: • 1919 – The form of government in the Republic of Finland is officially confirmed. For this reason, July 17 is known as the Day of Democracy (Kansanvallan päivä) in Finland.[8]

events.description: Altona Bloody Sunday: A riot between the Nazi Party paramilitary forces, the SS and SA, and the German Communist Party ensues.
events.html: • 1932 – Altona Bloody Sunday: A riot between the Nazi Party paramilitary forces, the SS and SA, and the German Communist Party ensues.

events.description: Spanish Civil War: An Armed Forces rebellion against the recently elected leftist Popular Front government of Spain starts the civil war.
events.html: • 1936 – Spanish Civil War: An Armed Forces rebellion against the recently elected leftist Popular Front government of Spain starts the civil war.

events.description: Douglas Corrigan takes off from Brooklyn to fly the "wrong way" to Ireland and becomes known as "Wrong Way" Corrigan.
events.html: • 1938 – Douglas Corrigan takes off from Brooklyn to fly the "wrong way" to Ireland and becomes known as "Wrong Way" Corrigan.

events.description: Port Chicago disaster: Near the San Francisco Bay, two ships laden with ammunition for the war explode in Port Chicago, California, killing 320.
events.html: • 1944 – Port Chicago disaster: Near the San Francisco Bay, two ships laden with ammunition for the war explode in Port Chicago, California, killing 320.

events.description: World War II: At Sainte-Foy-de-Montgommery in Normandy, Field Marshal Erwin Rommel is seriously injured by Allied aircraft while returning to his headquarters.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: At Sainte-Foy-de-Montgommery in Normandy, Field Marshal Erwin Rommel is seriously injured by Allied aircraft while returning to his headquarters.[9]

events.html: • 1945 – World War II: The main three leaders of the Allied nations, Winston Churchill, Harry S. Truman and Joseph Stalin, meet in the German city of Potsdam to decide the future of a defeated Germany.

events.description: The largest number of United States midshipman casualties in a single event results from an aircraft crash in Florida, killing 44.
events.html: • 1953 – The largest number of United States midshipman casualties in a single event results from an aircraft crash in Florida, killing 44.

events.description: First Indochina War: Viet Minh troops successfully ambush the armoured French column 'G.M. 42' in the Battle of Chu Dreh Pass in the Central Highlands. It is the last battle of the war.
events.html: • 1954 – First Indochina War: Viet Minh troops successfully ambush the armoured French column 'G.M. 42' in the Battle of Chu Dreh Pass in the Central Highlands. It is the last battle of the war.[10]

events.html: • 1962 – Nuclear weapons testing: The "Small Boy" test shot Little Feller I becomes the last atmospheric test detonation at the Nevada National Security Site.

events.description: Abdul Rahman Arif is overthrown and the Ba'ath Party is installed as the governing power in Iraq with Ahmed Hassan al-Bakr as the new Iraqi President.
events.html: • 1968 – Abdul Rahman Arif is overthrown and the Ba'ath Party is installed as the governing power in Iraq with Ahmed Hassan al-Bakr as the new Iraqi President.

events.description: King Mohammed Zahir Shah of Afghanistan, while having surgery in Italy, is deposed by his cousin Mohammed Daoud Khan.
events.html: • 1973 – King Mohammed Zahir Shah of Afghanistan, while having surgery in Italy, is deposed by his cousin Mohammed Daoud Khan.

events.html: • 1976 – East Timor is annexed and becomes the 27th province of Indonesia.

events.description: The opening of the Summer Olympics in Montreal is marred by 25 African teams boycotting the games because of New Zealand's participation. Contrary to rulings by other international sports organizations, the IOC had declined to exclude New Zealand because of their participation in South African sporting events during apartheid.
